This article is a Presidential Memorandum from December 23, 2016, regarding the order of succession within the National Endowment for the Arts. The memorandum states that certain officials within the National Endowment for the Arts will act as the Chairperson of the organization if the Chairperson is unable to perform their duties. The order of succession is as follows: Senior Deputy Chairman, Deputy Chairman for Management and Budget, Chief of Staff, and Director of Strategic Communications and Public Affairs. The memorandum also includes exceptions and provisions, such as the President's discretion to designate an acting Chairperson and the lack of enforceable rights or benefits.